  "description": "Undersea telegraph and telephone cables connecting continents. Gutta-percha insulation (natural latex from Palaquium gutta, dielectric strength 15-25 kV/mm), armored cable construction, cable-laying ships, deep-sea repair operations, and signal amplification. Bandwidth: 1-2 WPM on early transatlantic cables (1858), improving to 100+ WPM with mirror galvanometer and siphon recorder. The first global communications infrastructure.",
